Utorrent with a regular torrent file normally has the "info" of what you are downloading, such as the files/movies/folders and puts it in your preferred saved directory.  

With a Magnet link, it starts Utorrent, but you need to tell it where to save ei; "C:torrents" or what ever, but not just "c:" it needs that "".  It will also not show the files it will download until it starts and downloads the files's info.

Also, I have found that some files also deny access for some reason.  Don't know why yet, but I usually just pick a different source then.
